<!DOCTYPE task PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DITA Task//EN" "task.dtd">
<task id="task_cgq_1gj_cs">
    <title>Creating a new thesaurus entry</title>
    <taskbody>
        <context>The main function of the Thesaurus is to provide standardized vocabulary for the
            text metadata (extra-textual information), like dating, location or material. For a
            detailed description of the individual elements of the Thesaurus view see <xref
                href="oberflaeche_thesaurus.dita"/>.</context>
        <steps>
            <step>
                <cmd>Open the Thesaurus view by clicking the <image
                        href="Images/icons/full/icon16/thss.png" id="image_fck_tgj_cs"/> "Thesaurus"
                    icon in the <xref href="oberflaeche_toolbar_e3.dita"/>.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>In the Thesaurus Navigator on the left, click either <image
                        href="Images/icons/full/icon16/thss_add.png" id="image_vbs_52k_qr"/> "Add
                    Thesaurus Root Entry" or <image href="Images/icons/full/icon16/ths-add.png"
                        id="image_v3d_w2k_qr"/> "Add Thesaurus Child Entry". A root entry is an
                    umbrella key word, while the child entry may stand on its own or have other
                    children. </cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Click on the Thesaurus entry to edit its content. A Passport Editor <image
                        href="Images/icons/full/icon16/passport.png" id="image_ott_5fk_qr"/> will
                    appear in the middle.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>In the Passport Editor you can type in a name (default name is either
                    "Thesaurus Root" or "Thesaurus Child"), define type and subtype via the dropdown
                    menus and edit visibility and review status. For a detailed description of the
                    individual tabs and elements of the passport editor of the Thesaurus, see <xref
                        href="oberflaeche_thesaurs_passporteditor.dita"/>.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>To add an annotation or a comment to a Thesaurus entry, click <image
                        href="Images/icons/full/icon16/annotation-add.png" id="image_yky_5vm_wr"/>
                    "Add Annotation" and <image href="Images/icons/full/icon16/comment-add.png"
                        id="image_st5_vvm_wr"/> "Add Comment" in the toolbar of the Thesaurus
                    Navigator. </cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>To delete a thesaurus entry, use the <image
                        href="Images/icons/full/obj16/delete.png" id="image_xdl_2wm_wr"/> "Delete"
                    button in the Thesaurus Navigator toolbar. It will move an entry to the bin,
                    where you can manually permanently delete it. Closing or restarting the BTS will
                    also lead to the permanent deletion of an entry from the Bin.</cmd>
            </step>
        </steps>
    </taskbody>
</task>
